<subSubSection pageId="96" pageNumber="97" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="96" pageNumber="97">
Perennial herb from a central taproot with trailing stems to 1 m, plant adpressed pubescent to glabrescent. Leaves petiolate, 1-2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.4-05 cm, lanceolate-deltoid, acute, margin entire to slightly undulate, base shallowly cordate and auriculate, the auricles entire or bifid; petioles 3-8 mm long. Flowers solitary, pedunculate, axillary, becoming recurved in fruit; peduncles mostly 1-2 cm long; bracteoles filiform, 1-1.5 mm; pedicels 3-12 mm; outer sepals 2-3(-4) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 mm, obovate to broadly elliptic, rounded and minutely apiculate, scarious, glabrous or thinly appressed pubescent; inner sepals similar; corolla 5-7 mm long, white or pink, very shallowly lobed, midpetaline bands almost glabrous except for a few hairs at apex; ovary glabrous; style glabrous, divided c. 2 mm above base, stigmas c. 1.5-2 mm. Capsule glabrous; seeds coarsely and irregularly tuberculate. [
<bibRefCitation author="Johnson, RW" journalOrPublisher="Austrobaileya" pageId="204" pageNumber="205" pagination="408 - 411" refId="B166" refString="Johnson, RW, 1987. Two new species of Convolvulus L. (Convolvulaceae) from South Australia. Austrobaileya 2: 408 - 411" title="Two new species of Convolvulus L. (Convolvulaceae) from South Australia." volume="2" year="1987">Johnson 1987</bibRefCitation>
: 410-411, figure 1; 
<bibRefCitation author="Johnson, RW" journalOrPublisher="Austrobaileya" pageId="204" pageNumber="205" pagination="1 - 39" refId="B167" refString="Johnson, RW, 2001. A taxonomic revision of Convolvulus L. (Convolvulaceae) in Australia. Austrobaileya 6: 1 - 39" title="A taxonomic revision of Convolvulus L. (Convolvulaceae) in Australia." volume="6" year="2001">Johnson 2001</bibRefCitation>
: 10, figs 3-4, map 1].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
