1852).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="96" pageNumber="97" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Very distinctive because of the tiny calyx, lanceolate-deltoid leaves with basal auricles and the distinctive seed ornamentation.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
